
Ranger Help for: enemy
======================

SUMMARY:    
Each Ranger has a special species that he or she just loaths. Use the
'setenemy' command to set your enemy species. A Ranger's primary terrain
determines what races are allowed. Once set, the Ranger will get fighting
bonuses and stronger Ranger attack-skill damage against it. In combat this
currently means a major boost to critical chance (currently +30 crit) and
a sizable damage increase when striking that species (currently about
+33% damage). There are also some hinderances,
such as you probably won't be able to sooth an orc, if an orc is your
enemy race. Your enemy species will never be the race of your follower.

Use 'setenemy' with no argument to see the choices available to your
primary terrain. Use 'rhelp <species>' or 'rhelp enemy <species>' to read
what that species usually covers before choosing.

=============================================================================
SEE ALSO: setenemy, setprime and followers
